        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
            "@type": "School",
            "name": "Lokseva E School - Pashan"
          },
          "author": {
            "@type": "Person",
            "name": "Ana Thite"
          },
          "datePublished": "2023-04-21",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "1",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Very disappointed with school management and teachers. My kid was here up to 5th std. Initially school was good, and staff was stable, focused on extracurricular activities also (up to 2018-19). But before pandemic, condition got worst day by day. After pandemic also, many good teachers left the school. Maths, Science, Marathi teachers changed so many times till now. School time is for 8 hours but 1 or 2 lectures goes off each day. Last year and this year, not any single sport competition (annual sport day), annual gathering, science activities were not happened. Only single field trip happened at same earlier location called \"Lekha Farm\". Even kids have not enjoyed it. Fortunately, we got few good teachers.  There is a crucial problem of teacher's salary, that's why good teachers are leaving school within a year. If your child is self-motivated and doing study hard then only go for this school, otherwise, his future will be at risk. I am writing this detailed review so, no one will suffer like me. Giving one star for only those few sincere teachers.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
        {
